          "comment": "Won this race last year and could make a bold bid in defence of her crown; cheekpieces on",
          "spotlight": "Won this race (good to firm) last year and ended her 4yo campaign with a second to stablemate Friendly Soul in the Group 1 Prix de l'Opera at Longchamp (1m2f, very soft); hasn't found her A-game in two runs this season but her second at Haydock (10.4f Listed) last time was a respectable effort; seems to be working her way back towards her peak and it wouldn't be a surprise if she made a bold bid in defence of her crown; cheekpieces added.",
          "medical": [],
          "quotes": [
            {
              "date": "2024-06-19",
              "horse": "Running Lion",
              "horse_id": "4431787",
              "race": "Duke Of Cambridge Stakes (Group 2) (Fillies & Mares)",
              "race_id": "865760",
              "course": "Ascot",
              "course_id": "crs_52",
              "distance_f": "8",
              "distance_y": "1753",
              "quote": "Running Lion has been unlucky. Moves a bit soon in the Dahlia Stakes at Newmarket, gets boxed in at Epsom. We did decide, third time, Oisin, do what you want. He's drawn 11, go to the front, control it. It was perfect, because we got in a muddle in the last two races - John Gosden, joint-trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2023-08-16",
              "horse": "Running Lion",
              "horse_id": "4431787",
              "race": "British EBF 40th Anniversary Upavon Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)",
              "race_id": "845792",
              "course": "Salisbury",
              "course_id": "crs_1352",
              "distance_f": "10",
              "distance_y": "2181",
              "quote": "Running Lion had a bad experience in both the Oaks and French Oaks, when she got sunstroke and the wobbles. I haven't trained her hard for this and she's run a lovely race. I think we've got something to build on now - John Gosden, joint-trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2023-05-07",
              "horse": "Running Lion",
              "horse_id": "4431787",
              "race": "Howden Pretty Polly Stakes (Listed Race) (Fillies)",
              "race_id": "837025",
              "course": "Newmarket",
              "course_id": "crs_988",
              "distance_f": "10",
              "distance_y": "2200",
              "quote": "It will be very interesting with Running Lion if she's more Prix de Diane (French Oaks) or if she's an Oaks mile-and-a-half filly. We'll have to give that a bit of thought. It's lovely to have a filly like this. It's testing ground out there and they've got to be able to handle it. Full marks for her doing it so well. The jockey's first reaction was to possibly stay at a mile and a quarter - John Gosden, joint-trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2023-04-10",
              "horse": "Running Lion",
              "horse_id": "4431787",
              "race": "Racing TV Fillies' Conditions Stakes (GBB Race)",
              "race_id": "835960",
              "course": "Kempton (AW)",
              "course_id": "crs_28054",
              "distance_f": "8",
              "distance_y": "1760",
              "quote": "That was a nice performance. I thought Running Lion showed a great attitude and we'd be happy at a mile for the moment Oisin said, but a mile and a quarter would be no problem in the future. We're delighted with her and she's tough and genuine. We don't have to go anywhere in a hurry; we'll see how she is in the next couple of weeks and take it from there - John Gosden, joint-trainer."
            }
          ],
