          "owner": "Highclere Thoroughbred Racing - Da Vinci",
          "owner_id": "own_1312484",
          "prev_trainers": [],
          "prev_owners": [],
          "comment": "Held off Crimson Advocate in Listed race at Kempton but she's exposed and this looks tough",
          "spotlight": "Her highlights last season included a win in the Sandringham at Royal Ascot (1m, good to firm) and a clearcut success in Group 3 at Deauville (1m, good) in August; made virtually all when just holding off Crimson Advocate on Kempton reappearance (1m Listed) in March but she's exposed after 16 starts and has something to find on the figures back in a Group 2.",
          "medical": [
            {
              "date": "2023-10-19",
              "type": "Wind Surgery"
            }
          ],
          "quotes": [
            {
              "date": "2025-03-29",
              "horse": "Soprano",
              "horse_id": "4924622",
              "race": "Virgin Bet Snowdrop Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)",
              "race_id": "889561",
              "course": "Kempton (AW)",
              "course_id": "crs_28054",
              "distance_f": "8",
              "distance_y": "1760",
              "quote": "Soprano has proven she's a Group 1 filly and George was keen to come here. William [Buick] said she's too gassy and fresh, but she gave him a terrific feel. When he asked her to put the race to bed, despite running so free, she really kicked. I think that's what we want to take out of this. Royal Ascot is so important to all of us, so definitely that will be the plan and I think all races lead there - Harry Herbert, managing director of Highclere Racing, owners."
            },
            {
              "date": "2024-08-15",
              "horse": "Soprano",
              "horse_id": "4924622",
              "race": "Prix de Lieurey - Fonds Europeen de l'Elevage (Group 3) (3yo Fillies) (Round Course) (Turf)",
              "race_id": "874617",
              "course": "Deauville",
              "course_id": "crs_5356",
              "distance_f": "8",
              "distance_y": "1760",
              "quote": "Soprano has always promised a lot and I think that being ridden differently today was the key to her success. William [Buick] got her out smartly from her wide draw and it enabled him to get that good position. She's a strong stayer at the mile and now she's a Group 3 winner as well as a Royal Ascot winner. She was littered with black type as a two-year-old and it was good to get that Group-race win. She's always been well entered and she's in the Matron. She'll probably fly the flag at Group 1 level at some stage but it was really all about today - George Boughey, trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2024-06-21",
              "horse": "Soprano",
              "horse_id": "4924622",
              "race": "Sandringham Stakes (Fillies' Handicap)",
              "race_id": "869194",
              "course": "Ascot",
              "course_id": "crs_52",
              "distance_f": "8",
              "distance_y": "1760",
              "quote": "Saying that this filly has been unlucky wouldn't quite quantify it, but huge credit has to go to Harry [Herbert] - we had a long phone conversation in the office the other morning. I wanted to go to Carlisle and Harry wanted to come to Ascot! She's been a filly we've always held in really high regard. Leaving Epsom, I called Harry and said we're going to the Sandringham - we've got to go, we've got to try the mile. Soprano hit the line so strong at Musselburgh. Again, huge credit must go to Charles Eddery - he's ridden her since she came to us as a yearling, and she'd been difficult. She's been a bit keen and a bit numb, and Billy did a great job settling her there but she's taken a while to relax at home, and just as I was saddling her today, as a two-year-old she was mauling me and today she stood there quiet as a lamb. She's coming of age now, just like her jockey - George Boughey, trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2023-06-23",
              "horse": "Soprano",
              "horse_id": "4924622",
              "race": "Albany Stakes (Group 3) (Fillies)",
              "race_id": "841952",
              "course": "Ascot",
              "course_id": "crs_52",
              "distance_f": "6",
              "distance_y": "1320",
              "quote": "I am delighted with Soprano. She looked like she was probably drawn on the wrong side unfortunately, but we are thrilled. She's a filly that is always going to get further. She's out of a sister to a Breeders' Cup Mile winner and that's where her future lies, probably up in trip. They just had a little bit too much toe for her and sprinted away, but she hit the line strong - George Boughey, trainer."
            }
          ],
          "stable_tour": [
            {
              "horse": "Soprano",
              "horse_id": "4924622",
              "quote": "This has been the plan for a long time after her Sandringham win last season. She was good on her return on the all-weather at Kempton, beating Crimson Advocate by a nose. She doesn't carry a penalty in the Duke of Cambridge and it's a logical next step. The fillies' programme over a mile doesn't lend itself that well to the first half of year, so she'll be campaigned into the summer and the second half of the season. 09-06-25"
            },
            {
              "horse": "Soprano",
              "horse_id": "4924622",
              "quote": "A lovely filly who was quick enough to win on her debut over 5f at Newmarket on Guineas weekend. She's in good shape and has been training good and the 6f of the Albany would suit her well. Her work has continued to impress since Newmarket, and I believe the track next week will suit. She is very relaxed at home and took the crowds well on the Rowley Mile. I'm hopeful she will have a big shout next week. 14-06-23"
            }
          ],
