          "comment": "Swooped for C&D Champion win; travelled much the better when 2nd to Los Angeles on return",
          "spotlight": "7yo who's won two of his three attempts at Group 1; swooped to overcome trouble in running in the Champion Stakes over C&D (soft) last October and he was travelling much the better when he headed Los Angeles just inside the final 1f in Tattersalls Gold Cup at the Curragh (10.5f, officially good) last month, only to lose out in the last ten strides; three of his wins at lower levels were on good to firm; should be primed to throw down a telling late bid.",
          "medical": [],
          "quotes": [
            {
              "date": "2025-05-25",
              "horse": "Anmaat",
              "horse_id": "3293700",
              "race": "Tattersalls Gold Cup (Group 1)",
              "race_id": "891111",
              "course": "Curragh",
              "course_id": "crs_4628",
              "distance_f": "10.5",
              "distance_y": "2310",
              "quote": "It was a heck of a run, the lack of a run just told. Put it this way, I look forward to taking him [Los Angeles] on again now Anmaat has a run under his belt - Owen Burrows, trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2024-10-19",
              "horse": "Anmaat",
              "horse_id": "3293700",
              "race": "Qipco Champion Stakes (British Champions Middle Distance) (Group 1)",
              "race_id": "873079",
              "course": "Ascot",
              "course_id": "crs_52",
              "distance_f": "10",
              "distance_y": "2200",
              "quote": "Anmaat is unbelievable. He's always gone under the radar. It was touch and go whether he'd run in this race, and we came here to finish third or fourth behind Economics and Calandagan. To go and do what he did, it's great. The first half went perfectly as I wanted to sit third or fourth and give myself an option, but I could see early on Los Angeles wasn't taking Ryan [Moore] on at all. When we turned into the straight I had horses on my outside keeping me in and we just had to try and work our way through. We just got completely stopped, there was no option b or c at the time. We were just stuck, but when he got the gap it was extraordinary the way he picked up - Jim Crowley, jockey, speaking to Racing TV."
            },
            {
              "date": "2024-08-10",
              "horse": "Anmaat",
              "horse_id": "3293700",
              "race": "Betfred Rose Of Lancaster Stakes (Group 3)",
              "race_id": "872198",
              "course": "Haydock",
              "course_id": "crs_598",
              "distance_f": "10.5",
              "distance_y": "2300",
              "quote": "Anmaat had to be game, he just got a bit tired but he was entitled to after 439 days off. He needed a run last year to hit peak form so fingers crossed he comes out of this okay. He's in the Irish Champion but we'll let the dust settle after this and have a chat with Sheikha Hissa, Richard Hills and Angus Gold and go from there. It was a complex foot injury and all the team has done a great job to get him back - Owen Burrows, trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2023-05-29",
              "horse": "Anmaat",
              "horse_id": "3293700",
              "race": "Prix d'Ispahan (Group 1) (4yo+) (Grande Course) (Turf)",
              "race_id": "842479",
              "course": "Longchamp",
              "course_id": "crs_5486",
              "distance_f": "9.5",
              "distance_y": "2035",
              "quote": "Anmaat is pretty laid back about life so he'll never win by a couple of lengths. He doesn't show a huge amount at home but he's bloody tough. The ground was as quick as we'd want to go in today but he doesn't half travel, even on this ground - Owen Burrows, trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2023-05-07",
              "horse": "Anmaat",
              "horse_id": "3293700",
              "race": "bet365 Gordon Richards Stakes (Group 3)",
              "race_id": "840017",
              "course": "Newmarket",
              "course_id": "crs_988",
              "distance_f": "10",
              "distance_y": "2200",
              "quote": "It was a solid run. I thought we were up against it giving 5lb to Adayar and he's run his race. Anmaat needed to get his season started so I thought it was a good solid run. He battled away and it's tough out there, it's hard work. He's obviously in the Tattersalls Gold Cup in around three weeks' time and the Prix d'Ispahan in France, so we'll see how he comes out of this. We might try him over a little bit further at some stage. I don't know when but we'll see - Owen Burrows, trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2022-08-06",
              "horse": "Anmaat",
              "horse_id": "3293700",
              "race": "Betfred Rose Of Lancaster Stakes (Group 3)",
              "race_id": "816779",
              "course": "Haydock",
              "course_id": "crs_598",
              "distance_f": "10.5",
              "distance_y": "2300",
              "quote": "It was a big performance from Anmaat to win first time up at York and he had pleased me since. What surprised me was how far he travelled on the bridle, he's obviously really improving but we didn't expect that. We were stepping out of handicap company and I'm not sure where we'll go next, they'll be nice discussions to have. It was quick at York but interestingly Jim [Crowley] thought the bit of juice in the ground suited him - Owen Burrows, trainer."
            }
          ],
          "stable_tour": [
            {
              "horse": "Anmaat",
              "horse_id": "3293700",
              "quote": "He's fine after Ireland, where he was narrowly beaten in the Tattersalls Gold Cup. He did everything right bar win, but the winner [Los Angeles] had race-fitness and it just told in the last 50 yards. I was thrilled with him and you don't see many travel in Group 1s the way he did. It was a proper race and we were chuffed to bits with him. He's come out of it well and, as long as it's not rattling quick ground, then we'll be heading there. 10-06-25"
            },
            {
              "horse": "Anmaat",
              "horse_id": "3293700",
              "quote": "He has done nothing but progress all through his career, winning seven of his 12 starts with four seconds and a third. You don't get much more genuine than that and it has been a wonderful journey so far. Last year he started off on 103 in July but by the time he had wrapped up the campaign he had won three straight races including the Group 2 Prix Dollar on Arc weekend at Longchamp. He had a very good winter and I was keen to get a Group 1 under his belt, so we targeted the Prix d'Ispahan. He had a very pleasing return when second to Adayar while having to concede 5lb, which was no bad effort. It brought him to just where I wanted and we took the chance of going to France, where you know they can go very slow and then sprint. Thankfully he's very agile and has a great cruising speed and turn of foot. The ground was certainly faster by race time than it was advertised in the morning, but it didn't seem to be a problem, although I wouldn't want to run him on anything quicker. We spoke to Angus [Gold, Shadwell's racing manager] about Royal Ascot and the Prince of Wales's Stakes, but we thought it best to give him an extra couple of weeks after that and look at the Eclipse. Then he would have the obvious targets like the Juddmonte, Irish Champion and ultimately the Champion Stakes at Ascot in October. He put in a career-best performance last time and I don't think he has stopped improving yet. 07-06-23"
            }
          ],
