          "comment": "Career has taken some disappointing turns; looks set for a front-running role at big price",
          "spotlight": "2023 was his heyday, when winning the St Leger and fifth in the Arc; career has taken some disappointing turns since last autumn and he could be set for a front-running role at a big price today, as on his last two starts.",
          "medical": [],
          "quotes": [
            {
              "date": "2025-02-22",
              "horse": "Continuous",
              "horse_id": "4493098",
              "race": "Longines Red Sea Turf Handicap (Group 2) (3yo+) (Inner Track) (Turf)",
              "race_id": "888872",
              "course": "Riyadh",
              "course_id": "crs_26416",
              "distance_f": "15",
              "distance_y": "3300",
              "quote": "Continuous ran very well. It was his first run back, so happy with him - Ryan Moore, jockey."
            },
            {
              "date": "2024-08-17",
              "horse": "Continuous",
              "horse_id": "4493098",
              "race": "Shoda Market Cafe Royal Whip Stakes (Group 3)",
              "race_id": "873505",
              "course": "Curragh",
              "course_id": "crs_4628",
              "distance_f": "10",
              "distance_y": "2200",
              "quote": "Continuous has loads of options. He could go to the Irish Champion Stakes or the Irish St Leger. He could run in the Irish Champion with a view to going to the Arc. He could go to the Japan Cup He is a very versatile horse and a great one to have. Dropping him back to this trip was not a worry. We decided we would take a lead today if we could. He could have popped out in front and done it all himself. He's a classy horse and an unusual type of horse and a very genuine horse. He can do it from 1m2f and possibly up to 2m - Aidan O'Brien, trainer"
            },
            {
              "date": "2023-10-01",
              "horse": "Continuous",
              "horse_id": "4493098",
              "race": "Qatar Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe (Group 1) (3yo+ No Geldings) (Grande) (Turf)",
              "race_id": "841224",
              "course": "Longchamp",
              "course_id": "crs_5486",
              "distance_f": "12",
              "distance_y": "2640",
              "quote": "I was very happy. We made the decision to take our time and relax, and Continuous dropped in lovely. The pace was very slow so they sprinted in the last two or three furlongs. He was coming through, but obviously the winner quickened up on the outside. He's probably best over a strongly run mile and a half. He could go to Japan, Hong Kong, America or Dubai. All those things are open to him. He's a ready-made four-year-old and we think the best is yet to come - Aidan O'Brien, trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2023-09-16",
              "horse": "Continuous",
              "horse_id": "4493098",
              "race": "Betfred St Leger Stakes (Group 1) (British Champions Series) (No Geldings)",
              "race_id": "844269",
              "course": "Doncaster",
              "course_id": "crs_390",
              "distance_f": "14.5",
              "distance_y": "3195",
              "quote": "You would say looking at him at York, he was nailed on for this race and he had form on soft ground. Continuous didn't have any problem with the trip. He's got a lot of class, you could see it in his work every day. We're over the moon. The lads will think about the Arc, I'd say, he handles soft ground and gets a mile and a half very well and has class. He has all the things that could work in an Arc. It's just whether the two-week turnback is too tight or not. He has a great constitution as well - Aidan O'Brien, trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2023-08-23",
              "horse": "Continuous",
              "horse_id": "4493098",
              "race": "Sky Bet Great Voltigeur Stakes (Group 2) (Colts & Geldings)",
              "race_id": "843301",
              "course": "York",
              "course_id": "crs_2782",
              "distance_f": "12",
              "distance_y": "2608",
              "quote": "Continuous came here in the Dante and he needed the run badly and ran a massive race. I said to Ryan before the race would any of the other horses have run as well in Dante as he did and he said they wouldn't. A little bit of class usually outs, especially if the pace is even. We thought he handles an ease very well because he has a little bit of a round action but that was fast ground today and he didn't seem to have any problem with it. He bends his knee but obviously that's his best performance so you have to say he's very comfortable on it. I asked Ryan and he said he doesn't need a mile and six but you wouldn't rule him out - Aidan O'Brien, trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2022-08-20",
              "horse": "Continuous",
              "horse_id": "4493098",
              "race": "Join Racing TV For Just 12 Euro A Month At racingtv.com Now Irish EBF Maiden",
              "race_id": "819431",
              "course": "Curragh",
              "course_id": "crs_4628",
              "distance_f": "7",
              "distance_y": "1540",
              "quote": "Continuous is still a baby. He seems to stay well and he quickened up quite well. He's in the Beresford Stakes and that's a possibility for him - Aidan O'Brien, trainer."
            }
          ],
