          "comment": "Powerful challenge took him to within a neck of victory in the Group 1 Ganay at Longchamp",
          "spotlight": "French-trained 4yo who won two Listed races last term but it's this year that he's really found his stride, winning over 1m2f in a Group 3 and Group 2 on first two outings, and Horizon Dore (third in this race last year) could not lay a glove on him in the latter on good ground (unraced on good to firm); powerful challenge took him to within a neck of victory in the Group 1 Ganay on latest outing and he's a serious player.",
          "medical": [],
          "quotes": [
            {
              "date": "2025-04-06",
              "horse": "Map Of Stars",
              "horse_id": "5381822",
              "race": "Prix d'Harcourt (Group 2) (4yo+) (Grande Course) (Turf)",
              "race_id": "892363",
              "course": "Longchamp",
              "course_id": "crs_5486",
              "distance_f": "10",
              "distance_y": "2200",
              "quote": "I think we have seen a real good one today. The way Map Of Stars went after that horse in front and the way he quickened is the sign of a top one. He also proved that he is maturing mentally and that is essential. We will follow the program and bring him back for the G1 Prix Ganay - Francis Graffard, trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2025-03-16",
              "horse": "Map Of Stars",
              "horse_id": "5381822",
              "race": "Prix Exbury (Group 3) (4yo+) (Turf)",
              "race_id": "890808",
              "course": "Saint-Cloud",
              "course_id": "crs_5694",
              "distance_f": "10",
              "distance_y": "2200",
              "quote": "In Map Of Stars's Listed win last October he ranged up to challenge very easily and then didn't put the race to bed straight away, only just doing enough. He doesn't have a lot of experience but it's great when they find everything so easy. I've no doubt he'll stay 2,400 metres and he deserves his chance in a good race up in trip. But for now he'll head to the Group 2 Prix d'Harcourt and, if he runs well there, the Ganay after that - Francis Graffard, trainer."
            }
          ],
          "stable_tour": [
            {
              "horse": "Map Of Stars",
              "horse_id": "5381822",
              "quote": "He's in great form and I've been very happy with him. His preparation has gone well and I expect to have him at his best for Ascot. It's a tough race but I think he's still progressing, while the horse who beat him in the Ganay [Sosie] has won another Group 1 since. 11-06-25"
            }
          ],
