          "comment": "Group 3 winner for the Gosdens; showed some promise on stable/seasonal debut",
          "spotlight": "Soft-ground Group 3 winner in 2023 for the Gosdens before losing his form; showed some promise (fifth to My Cloud) at Newbury on handicap/seasonal debut but needs to build on that effort.",
          "medical": [],
          "quotes": [
            {
              "date": "2023-08-04",
              "horse": "Epictetus",
              "horse_id": "4429422",
              "race": "Bonhams Thoroughbred Stakes (Group 3)",
              "race_id": "844939",
              "course": "Goodwood",
              "course_id": "crs_546",
              "distance_f": "8",
              "distance_y": "1760",
              "quote": "It took us three attempts at 1m2f to work out that he wants a mile! Epictetus showed plenty of speed over a mile at two, and we thought he was a horse who'd progress to 1m2f this year obviously that did not pan out - he has run good races but not what we thought that he was capable of. Dropping down in trip on ground that suited him worked today. Obviously there is a mile race back here, the Celebration Mile, which fits in well - Thady Gosden, joint-trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2023-04-25",
              "horse": "Epictetus",
              "horse_id": "4429422",
              "race": "Weatherbys Digital Solutions Blue Riband Trial (Listed Race)",
              "race_id": "836825",
              "course": "Epsom",
              "course_id": "crs_442",
              "distance_f": "10",
              "distance_y": "2217",
              "quote": "The ground was deep and Epictetus has not trained on anything like that this year. This has been the plan for him all year and we'll go to the Dante Stakes next. He may well be more of a Prix du Jockey Club horse but we'll see. Frankie said they went a good clip and he's shown a really good attitude We're still only getting ideas at this stage of the season and you can't judge him on that ground - John Gosden, joint-trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2022-10-22",
              "horse": "Epictetus",
              "horse_id": "4429422",
              "race": "Vertem Futurity Trophy Stakes (Group 1) (No Geldings)",
              "race_id": "819769",
              "course": "Doncaster",
              "course_id": "crs_390",
              "distance_f": "8",
              "distance_y": "1760",
              "quote": "I thought they might go that way, I was walking the track with Aidan and I told Frankie be careful, they're going to turn right out of the gate and use the stands' rail. Epictetus has run great. He's still an immature horse, he's still on the weak side and the ground found him out but he's a grand horse for next year. We'll start him out at a mile and a quarter in a trial, something like the Dante - John Gosden, joint-trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2022-07-08",
              "horse": "Epictetus",
              "horse_id": "4429422",
              "race": "Weatherbys British EBF Maiden Stakes (Colts & Geldings)",
              "race_id": "814869",
              "course": "Newmarket (July)",
              "course_id": "crs_4524",
              "distance_f": "7",
              "distance_y": "1540",
              "quote": "Epictetus wasn't wound up for the race and we have to be absolutely overjoyed with him. He was very professional and Martin (Harley) gave him a lovely ride. We'll probably go for another novice with him to gain some more experience. He'll be very comfortable over a mile - John Gosden, joint-trainer."
            }
          ],
