          "comment": "Creditable third in both runs this term but has nothing in hand off current mark",
          "spotlight": "Creditable third in notable 1m handicaps at Thirsk and York this season but may struggle to be placed, let alone succeed, in this hotter prize; well exposed 8yo who has nothing in hand off current mark.",
          "medical": [],
          "quotes": [
            {
              "date": "2024-08-03",
              "horse": "La Trinidad",
              "horse_id": "2829564",
              "race": "William Hill Summer Cup Handicap",
              "race_id": "872078",
              "course": "Thirsk",
              "course_id": "crs_2080",
              "distance_f": "8",
              "distance_y": "1758",
              "quote": "We'll have to go to York now. The ideal situation was to run well here and then go to York for the Clipper Handicap. We've won 13,000GBP for today which is great, though 77,000GBP for the Clipper would be a lot better, wouldn't it? I thought when La Trinidad came around the bend he was cruising, but I was hoping that Jonny didn't use his whip too soon. He waited and he gave him a really good ride. He used to ride him out all the time at home anyway, so he knows him well - Roger Fell, joint-trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2024-06-21",
              "horse": "La Trinidad",
              "horse_id": "2829564",
              "race": "In Loving Memory Of Michael Wood Handicap (Woodsmith Construction Group Straight Mile Series Quali')",
              "race_id": "869250",
              "course": "Redcar",
              "course_id": "crs_1222",
              "distance_f": "8",
              "distance_y": "1759",
              "quote": "I was waiting and didn't think it was going to happen for ten or so strides, but it opened up just in the nick of time and La Trinidad just got through. He's a decent horse. He's seven but still has a fair bit of ability and I think they all fancied him today. I hope he can keep on rocking and rolling - David Nolan, rider, speaking to Racing TV."
            },
            {
              "date": "2021-07-10",
              "horse": "La Trinidad",
              "horse_id": "2829564",
              "race": "John Smith's Racing Handicap",
              "race_id": "787212",
              "course": "York",
              "course_id": "crs_2782",
              "distance_f": "8",
              "distance_y": "1732",
              "quote": "La Trinidad is going the right way, I've always thought he was a good horse. We won't over-race him and he could win a nice race - Roger Fell, trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2021-06-12",
              "horse": "La Trinidad",
              "horse_id": "2829564",
              "race": "Ice Co Supporting Macmillan Handicap",
              "race_id": "784991",
              "course": "York",
              "course_id": "crs_2782",
              "distance_f": "9",
              "distance_y": "1937",
              "quote": "La Trinidad is a nice horse and he was down in class. Everyone keeps telling me we should go for the Cambridgeshire. He's definitely got a good engine and he's got a big handicap in him - Roger Fell, trainer."
            }
          ],
          "stable_tour": [
            {
              "horse": "La Trinidad",
              "horse_id": "2829564",
              "quote": "He's talented. He can sometimes not be the easiest to ride, he can do a bit too much in his races, so he likes a good pace to aim at and to come from nearer the back than the front. He won impressively off 85 at Doncaster last year and ran competitively in better races afterwards. Last year we aimed at the Straight-Mile Series Final at Redcar at the end of the season and we'll be doing something similar again. He finished second that day to Painters Palette, who was then sold for 165,000gns at the sales. The handicapper hasn't been very kind to us. He could do with being dropped 3lb or so. He could go to Redcar on Friday. 21-06-24"
            }
          ],
