          "comment": "Weakened in two 1m2f Listed races this year and is interesting back at 1m in cheekpieces",
          "spotlight": "Won a Listed race over 1m2f at Goodwood (good) last year but hasn't seen it out in two similar events over the same trip this season, so this drop back to 1m may help; also equipped with first-time cheekpieces and has Christophe Soumillon taking over in the saddle; no shock were she to go well from a fair mark based on her peak form.",
          "medical": [],
          "quotes": [
            {
              "date": "2024-05-25",
              "horse": "Francophone",
              "horse_id": "5230597",
              "race": "William Hill Height Of Fashion Stakes (Listed Race) (Fillies)",
              "race_id": "866759",
              "course": "Goodwood",
              "course_id": "crs_546",
              "distance_f": "10",
              "distance_y": "2177",
              "quote": "It was a bit of a gamble running Francophone back so quickly but she had come out of it in such good form that we took the chance and I'm delighted it's come off. It looked a good opportunity to get some bold black type and it's been a good week for the family as her aunt Madame Ambassador won a Listed race at Ayr on Wednesday. Whether she now steps up to a mile and a half for the Ribblesdale at Royal Ascot we'll have to see - Charlie Johnston, trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2024-04-28",
              "horse": "Francophone",
              "horse_id": "5230597",
              "race": "Best Odds Guaranteed At Planet Sport Bet Fillies' Handicap",
              "race_id": "864622",
              "course": "Southwell (AW)",
              "course_id": "crs_10244",
              "distance_f": "8",
              "distance_y": "1773",
              "quote": "Francophone was impressive first time out, should have won second time at Goodwood - or got it in the stewards' room - and was a bit inexperienced at Doncaster. She's a huge filly and we put her away for the year. Hopefully that's going to pay off this year because I'd like to think she'll be back in black type company at some point soon - Charlie Johnston, trainer."
            }
          ],
