          "comment": "Ready Naas win last month on only her third start for Stephen Thorne",
          "spotlight": "Cemented her positive start for this yard when drawing clear inside the final furlong under Jack Kearney at Naas (1m, good) last month; this is a much stronger race but she could have even more to offer for this stable.",
          "medical": [],
          "quotes": [
            {
              "date": "2025-05-18",
              "horse": "Independent Expert",
              "horse_id": "3880923",
              "race": "Nursery Of Champions Handicap",
              "race_id": "895735",
              "course": "Naas",
              "course_id": "crs_4992",
              "distance_f": "8",
              "distance_y": "1760",
              "quote": "The last day over seven, Independent Expert got a bit outpaced and stayed on well. Nowadays, the stiff mile suits her well. She was a good winner of a Killarney handicap last year on good to firm ground so we knew he'd handle it even though she handles juice in the ground as well. She's very tough, honest and genuine. The colours are important to me as they are my assistant Stephen Mooney's grandparents' silks. We'll opt for something similar, she might run well in one of those big fillies' handicaps on the big weekends as she has some good Curragh form and she'll be a nice filly for Galway as well - Stephen Thorne, trainer."
            },
            {
              "date": "2021-12-10",
              "horse": "Independent Expert",
              "horse_id": "3880923",
              "race": "Irish EBF Median Sires Series Fillies Maiden (IRE Incentive Race) (Div II)",
              "race_id": "800554",
              "course": "Dundalk (AW)",
              "course_id": "crs_29588",
              "distance_f": "7",
              "distance_y": "1540",
              "quote": "Indepenent Expert is a light little filly but the race conditions suited her. She was in well at the weights, so it's great she's a winner at two. It was a valuable race and the owner also has an incentive to buy another horse, getting a 10,000Euros voucher to buy a yearling at an Irish sale. That's it for this year, she ran well at Gowran on testing ground, so she could have a nice mark for turf handicaps early in the season - Andy Slattery, trainer."
            }
          ],
          "stable_tour": [
            {
              "horse": "Independent Expert",
              "horse_id": "3880923",
              "quote": "She won well at Naas in a handicap on Royal Ascot trials day and hit the line hard, so the Kensington Palace looks a suitable race. She might not have as much up her sleeve as my other horse as the handicapper knows her quite well, but she's not been long with us and hopefully she can keep improving. The stiff mile should suit her. 13-06-25"
            }
          ],
