              "course": "Haydock",
              "course_id": "crs_598",
              "distance_f": "5",
              "distance_y": "1100",
              "quote": "Alex gave Never Dark a really good ride. He had a feather weight and not many jockeys can do that weight so we were looking for a good apprentice who can claim. And he gave him a lovely, straightforward ride. We had him in at Ripon as well but it's undulating there and it doesn't suit every horse. The key to this horse is he handles dig in the ground and he's come to himself this year. He seems to have found a bit of confidence - Iain Jardine, trainer."
