          "comment": "Regressed and became inconsistent for Harry Fry; eased in grade for stable debut",
          "spotlight": "Very useful at his best for Harry Fry but has regressed and become inconsistent; not disgraced in Coral Cup at Cheltenham Festival (2m5f good to soft) on latest outing in March and, having changed hands for \u00a335,000 last month, is in much calmer waters for this stable debut; market may guide.",
          "medical": [],
          "quotes": [
            {
              "date": "2020-12-10",
              "horse": "Might I",
              "horse_id": "3314108",
              "race": "Wigley Group Daimler Powerhouse Standard Open National Hunt Flat Race (GBB Race)",
              "race_id": "771682",
              "course": "Warwick",
              "course_id": "crs_2210",
              "distance_f": "16",
              "distance_y": "3520",
              "quote": "Might I gave me a lovely feel and did everything the right way. I got there a mile too soon but he was very professional. I'd ridden him a bit at home and he doesn't show you an awful lot of boot, but he's come alive at the races and is clearly pretty talented - Lorcan Murtagh, jockey."
            }
          ],
          "stable_tour": [
            {
              "horse": "Might I",
              "horse_id": "3314108",
              "quote": "He hasn't taken to chasing this season and we're going to revert to hurdles with him. He was fourth in the Martin Pipe off top weight last season and we know he can be competitive off his current mark. He'll be much happier back over hurdles.  20-02-24"
            },
            {
              "horse": "Might I",
              "horse_id": "3314108",
              "quote": "It's surprising he only has a bumper and maiden hurdle to his name. We tried him at three miles first time out last season and he boiled over, then we got him spot on for a \u00a3100,000 race at the Winter Million meeting but it got abandoned and he had to go a week later in a \u00a330,000 handicap at Cheltenham on Trials day. He was a good fourth in the Martin Pipe but he'll switch to fences now and he has schooled really well, so he could make up for the frustrations of a few near-misses. He seems to be growing up, settling and maturing, so could well improve over fences. 04-10-23"
            }
          ],
