          "quotes": [
            {
              "date": "2021-12-26",
              "horse": "Glory And Fortune",
              "horse_id": "2418435",
              "race": "Ladbrokes Christmas Hurdle (Grade 1) (GBB Race)",
              "race_id": "799266",
              "course": "Kempton",
              "course_id": "crs_728",
              "distance_f": "16",
              "distance_y": "3520",
              "quote": "That was a massive run - but Glory And Fortune has thrown his handicap mark out of the window. I think they have just gone very fast on soft ground. I don't think he has improved 20lb, anyway - Stan Sheppard, rider."
            },
            {
              "date": "2019-01-01",
              "horse": "Glory And Fortune",
              "horse_id": "2418435",
              "race": "EBF Stallions & Cheltenham Pony Club (A Standard Open National Hunt Flat Race) (Listed Race)",
              "race_id": "718154",
              "course": "Cheltenham",
              "course_id": "crs_286",
              "distance_f": "14",
              "distance_y": "3069",
              "quote": "We're not going to overrace Glory And Fortune. It's all very well thinking festivals, but we want to look after him - look at the size of him. He's a huge, big unit and it wouldn't surprise me if we didn't run again this season. We'll see how he is in the spring, but he won't be out until mid- to the end of March. I think looking after him will help mentally and physically. he clearly has a huge amount of natural ability. The Aintree bumper could be a possibility, but I'd just be worried now about losing him mentally - Tom Lacey, trainer."
            }
          ],
          "stable_tour": [
            {
              "horse": "Glory And Fortune",
              "horse_id": "2418435",
              "quote": "I didn't think he ran too bad in the Greatwood Hurdle and I'm not sure he handles the undulations at Cheltenham. He's better than that and he's having a little break now. We'll look to run him through late spring and we may have another pop at the Betfair Hurdle at Newbury. 22-11-21"
            },
            {
              "horse": "Glory And Fortune",
              "horse_id": "2418435",
              "quote": "He lifted us to new heights last season when winning the Welsh Champion Hurdle and Betfair Hurdle. We took him back to Ffos Las last month, but the ground was too quick for him. We subsequently took him to Cheltenham for a hot Grade 2 novice chase where he jumped the first four fences like a seasoned handicapper, but when he missed the fence past the stands he went to pot. He's not an easy ride as he can throw his head back but I'll not be put off by that and we'll persevere over fences. We'll give him some intensive schooling over the next few weeks before hopefully bringing him back at Christmas. I've not lost any faith in him and believe he can be a very effective chaser. 30-11-22"
            }
          ],
